-- South African Coal Export Prices Decrease Most in Six Weeks
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-08-28T09:20:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/south-african-coal-export-prices-decrease-most-in-six-weeks.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, fell the most in six weeks.  Coal for  immediate delivery  decreased $1.98, or 2.2
percent, to $88.27 a metric ton in the week ended Aug. 24,
according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the
steepest decline since the week ended July 13. The price is
quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
